<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,213]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1966" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[684,964,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[684,811,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">A. nigripes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[821,964,188,213]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref280374" refString="Evans, H. E. (1966) A revision of the genus Anisepyris Kieffer (Hymenoptera. Bethylidae). Studia Entomologica, 9, 1 - 120." type="journal article">Evans, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body green metallic with blueish reflections; the mandible wide apically and angulate; the clypeus with the apical margin truncate and with two emarginations; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the circumocular suture present; and the pronotal disc with its transverse pronotal carina followed by a series of carinae, with a median pronotal line, and with the posterior pronotal sulcus distinctly wide, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[618,743,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[618,743,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">A. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dark green reflection and the metapectal-propodeal disc black; the mandible narrow, slightly angled, and with the lower tooth longer than the others; the clypeus with the median lobe rounded, short, and with an apical median tooth; the antennal scrobe carinate; the circumocular suture absent; and the pronotal disc without a transverse pronotal carina followed by a series of carinae, without a median pronotal line, and with the posterior pronotal sulcus narrow.
</paragraph>
